description:
&lt;p&gt;Advanced Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band: 8a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Derbyshire Community Health Services (DCHS) has been awarded outstanding overall community trust by CQC. We deliver care to 11 community hospitals and to patients in their own homes in Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Pharmacist to join our Medicines Management Team to help support patients and staff with all aspects of medicines optimisation and management. Based at Walton hospital in Chesterfield, this varied post provides a range of opportunities for a motivated pharmacist who is keen to develop their leadership skills within a key governance role, whilst maintaining clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties for this innovative post include leading on pharmacist medication reviews, with a focus on falls prevention, as part of the Trust&#39;s wider frailty agenda. Another key role will be the utilisation and analysis of ePACT2 reports to identify areas for improvement in the prescribing of more than 450 non-medical prescribers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunity to be involved in the wider programme of annual non-medical prescribing reviews and professional development events for DCHS non-medical prescribers, the update and delivery of medicines-related training for nurses and other healthcare professionals, the review of clinical guidelines and procedures, and representing the Medicines Management Team in meetings across the Trust and with other local NHS organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will also be opportunities to participate in the provision of pharmacy services to DCHS community hospitals, both on the wards and in the dispensary at Walton Hospital. Business mileage is paid by the Trust and there is free car parking at all DCHS hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent communication, organisational and interpersonal skills, be motivated and enthusiastic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications for full or part time: 30 to 37.5 hours per week will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julia Shaw, Principal Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
